I originally created a map named aim_pitfall for 1.5 CS about 5 years ago and wanted to sort of "recreate" it.  I'm actually excited about this one because you have to have some nerve if you want to get to the other side in a large firefight.  Or just luck :D  I changed some from the original unreleased version I made.  This map holds 18 on each side with AKs and M4s.  There's an AWP "prize" in the center on the middle beam if you have the nerve.  Grenades are also on the beam as well as in the pit.  If you fall into the pit as you're crossing because you get distracted, too drunk, or too high, well, your health lowers 76 points if you hit the ground and not the boxes below.  Grenades are in the pit to give you a fighting chance.  Buyzones for both sides are on the center beam if you don't die.  Good luck!

Map By siLenT. / TehSilence

Just a quick map I put together for small LAN parties with my mates, thought maybe the world would be interested in playing as well.

The small blocks are destroyable, and the camper shields on the top level have retractable shields. Weapons on the back wall of spawn have half ammo / quarter ammo / etc. for fairer gameplay, stopping people from just getting a more powerful gun and blasting away. 
Nevertheless, Enjoy!

Any feedback/ideas would be gladly accepted.

Send to cssmapfeedback@hotmail.com

Hello guys.
I am releasing my first larger aim_-Map today.
With aim_pistols_v1 you are able to train your pistol skills in case your primary runs dry.
You can play on this map with up to 24 players. Perfectly for public servers or big LAN's to warm up. :)

The map is full of crates, pillars and other obstacles that make good aim a must. Because of the angle of the sunlight there is alot of shadows on this map that make the flashlight helpful sometimes.
You can either stay with your starting pistol (USP/Glock) or try your luck with the Deagle and survive the round to get full Deagle ammo next round. -> Good skills will be rewarded!

**Please leave some constructive criticism and tell me how you find the map and why. :)**

Enjoy the map! :D
Please ask me before hosting this anywhere else, if you don't ask, at least give credit where its due.

Hey guys!
I am releasing my first CS:S map.
It's name is aim_pillars_v1, a very small map for a maximum of 6 players - perfectly for playing with friends or using it on a small public server to keep the players aim well. :)

There are alot of pillars on the map, which makes getting shots on target a real aiming challenge.
In addition, in the middle of the map is a large gap that separates the two spawns and cannot be passed without dying.
This forces you to keep distance to your enemy and you'll have to aim very accurate.
The pillars offer perfect cover against all kind of weapons, even AWP's will not hurt you if positioned behind a pillar.

Every team gets all the important weapons (M4, AK47, MP5, Deagle, AWP, Famas, HE-grenades ect. ...).

Attention:
I plan doing more versions of aim_pillar maps for a larger amount of players (12-20).
This was the very first map I ever created and i would really appreciate CONSTRUCTIVE criticism. ;)

Hey guys! Shortly after releasing my very basic map aim_pillars_v1 i played around with the light options a bit and some friends made suggestions what to make better. :)

There are alot of pillars on the map, which makes getting shots on target a real aiming challenge. In addition, in the middle of the map is a large gap that separates the two spawns and cannot be passed without dying. This forces you to keep distance to your enemy and you'll have to aim very accurate. The _night-Version also makes things a bit harder by making the map...darker (wow.). The flashlight can be a livesaver in some situations.
The pillars offer perfect cover against all kind of weapons, even AWP's will not hurt you if positioned behind a pillar.

Changelog:
This version isn't only a straight conversion to a nighttime map, it also contains **big balancing improvements**:
1. The terrorists now have 3 instead of 2 AK47's and 2 instead of 3 Glocks.
2. To get an AWP, you have to jump on the little bench (where the spawn weapons are) and duck-jump up to the big spawn-protection wall. Each team has 1 AWP.

Every team gets all the important weapons (M4, AK47, MP5, Deagle, AWP, Famas, HE-grenades ect. ...).

Attention: I plan doing more versions of aim_pillar maps for a larger amount of players (12-20). This is one of the first maps I ever created and i would really appreciate CONSTRUCTIVE criticism. ;)

**Enjoy!**

Special thanks go to Berkay aka RaZoR for having the idea to put the AWP up that wall. :)
